Why should I use a Bulk Wallet to accept EnergyCoins on my website?
The traditional approach to accepting EnergyCoins on your website requires that you install the official EnergyCoin client daemon ("energycoind"). Many website hosting packages don't support installing the EnergyCoin daemon. Also, running the EnergyCoin daemon on your web server means your private keys are hosted on the server and could get stolen if your web server is hacked. When using a Bulk Wallet you can upload only the EnergyCoin addresses and not the private keys to your web server. Then you don't have to worry about your EnergyCoin wallet being stolen if your web server is hacked.
How do I use a Bulk Wallet to accept EnergyCoins on my website?
  1. Use the Bulk Wallet tab to pre-generate a large number of EnergyCoin addresses (10,000+). Copy and paste the generated comma separated values (CSV) list to a secure text file on your computer. Backup the file you just created to a secure location.
  2. Import the EnergyCoin addresses into a database table on your web server. (Don't put the wallet/private keys on your web server, otherwise you risk hackers stealing your coins. Just the EnergyCoin addresses as they will be shown to customers.)
  3. Provide an option on your website's shopping cart for your customer to pay in EnergyCoin. When the customer chooses to pay in EnergyCoin you will then display one of the addresses from your database to the customer as his "payment address" and save it with his shopping cart order.
  4. You now need to be notified when the payment arrives. Google "EnergyCoin payment notification" and subscribe to at least one EnergyCoind payment notification service. There are various services that will notify you via Web Services, API, SMS, Email, etc. Once you receive this notification, which could be programmatically automated, you can process the customer's order. To manually check if a payment has arrived you can use Block Explorer. Replace THEADDRESSGOESHERE with the EnergyCoin address you are checking. It could take between 1 to 10 minutes for the transaction to be confirmed.
    http://explorer.energycoin.pw/address/THEADDRESSGOESHERE

  5. EnergyCoins will safely pile up on the block chain. Use the original wallet file you generated in step 1 to spend them.

Your EnergyCoin Private Key is a unique secret number that only you know. It can be encoded in a number of different formats. Below we show the EnergyCoin Address and Public Key that corresponds to your Private Key as well as your Private Key in the most popular encoding formats (WIF, HEX, B64, MINI).

EnergyCoin v0.6+ stores public keys in compressed format. The client now also supports import and export of private keys with importprivkey/dumpprivkey. The format of the exported private key is determined by whether the address was generated in an old or new wallet.
